    Dr Peter Kittel - Commodore Germany
    S Worley - Imagine artist
    Ben Williams - Black Belt programmer; HAM-E, Imagemaster
    Perry Kovowitz - ASDG; Art Department, Morph plus
    Jack Radigan - Author of JR Comm
    J Forgeas - Author of AZ
    Nicos Francis - Author of Power Packer
    Michael Swartz - Amiga Commercial Games Programmer

    The Amiga Graphics BBS is a public BBS with hundreds of daily messages
about Amiga computers, video work, 3d graphics, programming, games, hardware,
applications, reviews, audio, and telecommunications. Want to sell or buy
some hardware from Amigans around the Country? Want to hear more about the
68060 or the AGA Chip Set? Only Amiga Graphics BBS has all this.

    24 Hours (516) 473-6351 East Setauket, New York - Western Suffolk

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    November 2nd, 1992

    Please feel free to download the file list in the filebase under
misc/text/aga_file_list.lha. It is updated nightly. Also, we are now
receiving mailing lists both publically and privately, including news
from Imagine, Lightwave, Real3D, Commodore-Amiga, Excelsior BBS, AMOS,
Emplant, and more. I urge all callers to download the file in the filebase
under misc/text/america.lha. It will open your eyes to America's future
as a nation and a global leader, and is also updated on a regular basis.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    October 20th, 1992

    We are now offering FREE UNLIMITED DOWNLOADS for a limted time, for
all users! Upon validation of your account you are gauranteed free unlimited
downloads until mid-December 1992, when we will return to an upload/download
ratio as most BBS's have. New users are not gauranteed unlimited downloads
on their first call due to system limitations, but do have download privileges
and possibly unlimited credits.

